\ntime scale from minutes to days and observing run, but without any clear\ncorrelation or recognizable temporal pattern among the different lines. In the\ncase of H$\\alpha$ the CS contribution is also variable in just one of the\nobserving runs. We suggest that $\\phi$ Leo is a rapidly rotating $\\delta$ Scuti\nstar surrounded by a variable, (nearly) edge-on CS disk possibly re-supplied by\nthe $\\delta$ Scuti pulsations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Jun 2021 17:36:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-22"}
