es\nis often invisible in other wavelengths, like hard X-rays, presumably due to\nthe collisionless conditions in these regions of low ambient density and\nmagnetic field strength.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Jul 2021 03:05:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-29"}
