stem. More specifically, we\nfocus on our attention in the temperature ratio $T_1/T_2$ and the fourth degree\ncumulants $c_1$ and $c_2$ (measuring the departure of the velocity\ndistributions $f_1$ and $f_2$ from their Maxwellian forms). Finally, a linear\nstability analysis of the steady state solution is also carried out showing\nthat the steady state is always linearly stable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Jul 2021 08:12:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 3 Sep 2021 08:58:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-24"}
